messages.message: <!subteam^SQ3KR3V17> any volunteers to give an over of Instabase’s architecture and code to the interns joining next week?  :slightly_smiling_face:

Would love to to help with/shadow the overview! Someone with deeper knowledge about the broader architecture would be better to run point. Can definitely contribute a “My strategies for searching the codebase to figure things out on your own” portion though!
if it would be useful I could do a “deploying to *.instabase.com (http://instabase.com)” section
I would be interested in learning about the rest with the interns :smile:
would also be interested in helping/shadowing! could also contribute a core services section :slightly_smiling_face:
@shaunak would also love to listen in!

right now there is a “Specialties” section which we probably want to move into its own document — and we can guide people through different architectures in the codebase: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gev72qg1VVdpjOQzlV_J6Bke7VvM570mnVecE-GLivg/edit?folder=1tuDu6TfwGxc2Vi2alG4w6ufqdfIFdPPe
@dlluncor perfect!  Let’s coordinate — I was planning to making a slide deck for Instabase’s architecture so that we could repurpose it as we grow further
I would love to help out with this too
Happy to volunteer/and help with the slides. Can facilitate this for Interns in bangalore too
